hed a hateful attack. Saying that a person &quot;hates&quot; a long list of minority groups can have serious repercussions, even if untrue. At the very least it can lead to unannounced and unprovoked hostility from players in-game.<br>In attempting to make it clear that I am not such a hater, I came under further attack, as well as becoming embroiled in a pointless debate on a variety of issues which were irrelevant to my purpose.<br>I began receiving messages in-game from people reading and writing in the message board. I don't engage in such debates in-game. In-game, I play the game.<br>The threatening messages were not the most annoying, nor the most numerous. Those who wished to continue the debate in-game weren't even the most annoying. No, the most annoying were those who would drop me a tell or stop me during a port to tell me how they agreed with what I was saying in the message board.<br>Of course, the vast vast majority of them have been silent in the message board.<br>I'm tired.<br>I'm tired of fighting a campaign for decades with my neck out in the open, with everyone who even somewhat disagrees with me ready to take a swing at it, often directed at me rather than the issue, while others who claim to agree with me in private messages, behind the scenes, anonymous, safe, never step out to assert their agreement. Let alone bring fresh arguments and data with them into the fight. <br>I'm trying to figure out who I am that I should take the abuse this exposure gains me, and who are they that they can remain safe and secure in their anonymity. <br><br>So I'm going to retire to the shadows, myself. Let the most left-wing of idiots reign. Let left-wing dogma become Pravda. Alone and exposed, I can't win the battle, so the world is going to go that way in any event. If it's going to go that way in any event, I'm at least going to enjoy what fun I can have without having a bullseye on my forehead.<br><br>I've been accused of talking a lot in here. I do. It isn't considered that for every post I make, particularly in a controversial topic, I have 5 responses to deal with. It isn't considered that, even with only 5 responses, that's 10 eyes pouring over my statements searching for everything from logic errors, to typographical errors, to my 2 eyes searching their 5 messages; wasting half my time noting misrepresentations and misquotations of my remarks that must be addressed before I can address their (often foolish) arguments.<br><br>So I turn parasite. I intend reading these message boards for whatever information about the game they can gain me. But I don't see myself wasting any more time writing messages beyond announcing my availability for a given raid or other.<br>/sarcasm And of course, since I hate every division of mankind that can be imagined, there's not much point in my signing up for any raids, is there? <br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The answer is it's just like anything else, you take the good with the bad.<br>As far as the Aldrin soap box thing, well....you do type alot. <br><br>Lal <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Not anymore.<br> <p>Aldrin of the Nexus<BR><a href="http://www.xtimports.com/index.html"><img src="http://www.xtimports.com/data/Everquest/pics/Aldrinsig2.jpg" alt="Extra Terrestrial Imports " align="left" border="0" hspace="0" width="240" height="263"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udonedanaumni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Donedan Aumni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/25/02 8:12:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.furry.org.au/BornWild/ubb/avatar/Final_Fantasy_-_Devil_Mog.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign